-- Fedrigo Wins Stage 15 of Tour de France; Wiggins Keeps Race Lead
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-07-16T15:47:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/fedrigo-wins-stage-15-of-tour-de-france-wiggins-keeps-race-lead.html
France’s Pierrick Fedrigo won the
15th stage of cycling’s Tour de France. Bradley Wiggins keeps
the overall lead.  Today’s stage, a day before the final rest day, covered
158.5 kilometers (98 miles) from Samatan to Pau.  Wiggins finished in the main bunch today and remains on
course to become the first British winner of the Tour. The race
ends July 22 in Paris.  Today’s result was a fourth stage win for France this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 